thence S. 63-54′ E., 250.32 m. to point 4;

thence S. 0-49′ W., 58.53 m. to point 5;

thence S. 83-25′ W., 233.73 m. to point 6;

thence S. 82-26′ W., 138.73 m. to the point of

beginning, containing an area of SIXTY EIGHT THOUSAND ONE HUNDRED TWENTY (68,120) SQUARE METERS. All points referred to are indicated and are marked on the ground. Bearings true. This lot was surveyed in accordance with law and existing regulations promulgated thereunder by Leocadio S. Obedoza, Geodetic Engineer on February 4-5, 1980, and was approved by the Regional Director of Lands on November 6, 1980.

NOTE: This lot is identical to Lot 24218, a portion of Lot 4848, Cad-211, Santiago Cadastre.

